    "goal": "Make one user-visible capability run one lightweight, risk-based Better Plan lifecycle.",
    "description": "Scope: Closure: capability - generic lightweight Better Plan lifecycle. Context: per-Node mandatory category coverage and automatic acceptance redispatch can amplify one user request into repeated design/review cycles and adjacent capabilities. Target: use the selected Node as the sole lifecycle identity, keep acceptance proportional to real risks, return rejection or drift to the native main, stop after completion, and recommend quiet framework-owned waiting. Design Considerations: reuse the Node UUID and current acceptance mapping; change only next-action semantics and generic role guidance; preserve deterministic executor regression and thin audit. Design Value: Better Plan remains useful for design and verification without replacing the main agent's scope judgment. Constraints & Risks: no project/provider/platform special cases, timers, retry caps, new compatibility fields, automatic next-Node selection, broad regression, absolute paths, or runtime data.",
